blogData.description: Join VideoTranslatorAI as we showcase cutting-edge tech at the 2024 NSW Commercialisation Showcase, celebrating innovation and collaboration in NSW!

blogData.coverAlt: VideoTranslatorAI at the 2024 NSW Commercialisation Showcase

data.richContent:
We are thrilled to share our experience at the 2024 NSW Commercialisation Showcase, where VideoTranslatorAI had the honor of participating among a stellar lineup of innovative startups and scaleups in New South Wales.

Organized by the Office of the Chief Scientist & Engineer (OCSE), this event serves as a platform to celebrate and support companies that have benefited from OCSE programs.

About the Event

The 2024 NSW Commercialisation Showcase is a testament to the vibrant innovation ecosystem in NSW.

With over 30 dynamic companies spanning various sectors including deep tech, healthcare, quantum, sensing, environment, AgTech, communications, and emergency services, the event provided a unique opportunity for founders, investors, researchers, and industry leaders to connect and collaborate.

Experts from industry, academia, and government convened to discuss the importance of collaboration and explore ways in which the government can further support the commercialization and procurement of cutting-edge technologies.

VideoTranslatorAI's Participation

At our booth, we showcased our technology designed for both health and natural hazards. For health applications, we are proud to collaborate with Kiwako Ito, while for natural hazards, we work closely with Mel Taylor.

For those who couldn't attend the event or would like to learn more about our technology, we have prepared downloadable brochures for both health and natural hazards:

Health Brochure PDF
Natural Hazards Brochure PDF

Gratitude and Appreciation

A huge thank you to the Office of the Chief Scientist and Engineering for their support in making this possible and to everyone who visited our booth!

A special thank you to Crista Brocamonte, Carlos Carbonatto-Bowkett, and Aashna Rampal from OCSE, and also Nick Haskins and Catherine Oates Smith from NSSN, for their support and encouragement.

Conclusion

Participating in the 2024 NSW Commercialisation Showcase has been a remarkable experience for VideoTranslatorAI. We are deeply thankful to the Office of the Chief Scientist & Engineer for organizing this fantastic event and to all the attendees who stopped by our booth. 

We look forward to continuing our journey of innovation and collaboration in the NSW innovation ecosystem. Together, we can drive positive change and create a better future for all.
